tizzie
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a sixpenny piece (??occas. a shilling) (the 1873, 1984 cits reveal a play on TANNER and TIZZY, both contemp. colloq. for 6d)


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: also tizzy
